== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Halve @Potato Buns{2}. Thinly slice @Roma Tomato{1} into rounds.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @garlic powder{¾%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the garlic powder in the next step.)

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Onion ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1 tbsp onion, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt.

== Special Sauce ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @ketchup{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}.

== Griddled Onion ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Burger Patties ==

While onion cooks, form @ground beef{10%ounce} into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once onion is done, heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top each patty with @cheddar cheese{½%cup}; cover pan until cheese melts.

== Assembly ==

While cheese melts, toast buns until golden brown.

Stir pickled onion (draining first) into bowl with special sauce.

Fill toasted buns with patties, griddled onion, tomato, and special sauce. Divide burgers between plates; serve with potato wedges and any remaining sauce on the side for dipping.

> This burger falls in the GREAT category. The magic sauce is creamy, tangy, savory, and well... magical! You'll want to put it on everything, but it's especially awesome on the side with these crispy potato wedges.